   print(dim(normalized_vector))
   ```

### Java
In Java, you can use the `java.util.Vector` class to normalize the vector.

1. **Create or get the vector**:
   ```java
   import java.util.ArrayList;
   import java.util.Vector;
   import java.util.Arrays;

   public class Main {
       public static void main(String[] args) {
           Vector<Integer> vector = new Vector<>();
           vector.add(1);
           vector.add(2);
           vector.add(3);
       }

       public static void normalize(int[] vector) {
           int sum = 0;
           for (int num : vector) {
               sum += num;
           }
           int length = sum / (int) Math.sqrt(sum);
           for (int num : vector) {
               vector[num] /= length;
           }
       }
       public static void main(String[] args) {
           normalize(vector);
           System.out.println(Arrays.toString(vector));
       }
   }
   ```

